.TH "ca8210_config_extern_clk" 9 "ca8210_config_extern_clk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ca8210_config_extern_clk \- Configure the external clock provided by the ca8210
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ca8210_config_extern_clk
.BI "(struct ca8210_platform_data *pdata "  ","
.BI "struct spi_device *spi "  ","
.BI "bool on "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdata" 12
Pointer to ca8210_platform_data containing clock parameters
.IP "spi" 12
Pointer to target ca8210 spi device
.IP "on" 12
True to turn the clock on, false to turn off
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The external clock is configured with a frequency and output pin taken from
the platform data.
.SH "RETURN"
0 or linux error code
